de of Earth's dimension, she was destined to bring destruction upon it all, then have her memories washed away like sand in water. But over the years the magic had faded, and Sartha's will had been so strong as to fight the spell and keep the majority of the memories she had from Halon::<br>
<br>
&quot;Where...?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You are in the village of Halon. You passed out while riding in.&quot;<br>
<br>
::Sartha looked to the doorway where a woman stood. She seemed strangely familiar, but she could not quite place it::<br>
<br>
&quot;But how? Halon was burned to the ground, everyone was killed. No one survived to return and rebuild. I saw it all. So how?&quot;<br>
<br>
::the woman frowned::<br>
<br>
&quot;You seem to be mistaken. Halon has always stood in this very spot for as long as time has existed, which is forever as you know.&quot;<br>
<br>
::Sartha frowned and climbed to her feet, moving towards the door. She is stopped as the pain races through her body sharply, causing her to fall to her knees::<br>
<br>
&quot;You should stay in bed. You aren't well.&quot;<br>
<br>
::the woman moved to help her back to bed, but Sartha growled and pulled away, walking outside and looking around. Young children played in the streets and woman laughed and played tricks on each other. It was the typical Amazon village::<br>
<br>
&quot;This isn't right. Something's wrong. Dekim... he destroyed all of this. They all died. I saw it all. It can't be.&quot;<br>
<br>
::She fell to her knees again and Veyriean seemed to appear beside her as usual. She spoke on a thin mental line, obviously not showing that she was anymore than a simple tiger::<br>
<br>
&gt;&gt;I've scouted the terrain. There is another camp not far from here. They are all men. But the Amazons I have heard speaking seem to get along with this brother village. It is as if Karathea's tribe never existed. The Queen here is Kianna. I suggest you speak with her.&lt;&lt;<br>
<br>
::With that, Veyriean ran off again and Sartha headed towards the hut of the Queen:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/usheyala.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sheyala</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 77<br> <font color=#993300>(1/17/01 7:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=125.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ::Deep in the Forests:::</span><hr size=1> ::Just as Shey and Anya managed to tuck themselves away in the cave the demons rode by.  Shey lit a small torch and proceeded to a small niche in the cave.  After pulling a small catch in the wall, she motioned for Anya to follow her down the now showing secret passage::<br>
