&quot;Ah but Shey he is alive no longer but one of the most feared..he is a minion of..Hades.  A vampyre I think you call them?&quot;<br>
::With a gasp Shey looked away and squinted her eyes shut this was worse than anything that had ever happened...and by that she meant by FAR.  Shey wanted to speak more, but the demon turned around and ignored her until nightfall when the stufefd her up onto a horse, tied her feet into the stirrups and her hands to the pommel.  After many days of riding like this Shey longed for feeling in her wrists and ankles.  The cord she was tied with but into her ankles and wrists and the cold weather of the north scalded her skin.  She was the only one not dressed for the weather and she paid dearly for it::<br>
