<br>
&quot;We have to find a way out. If we don't, we're dead... I'm too weak to take us both over the wall or use my-&quot; ::she stopped herself abruptly from mentioning her powers and closed her mouth, peeking out from behind the hut. There was no way out::<br>
<br>
&quot;There is a tunnel on the side of the ruins. It was built years ago. When a sorceress was captured and chained as a sacrifice. They didn't know what she was. An amazon, the first in a long time, who was brave enough to despise and disreguard the men, freed her. The sorceress then made the tunnel for them to get safely out. But the Amazon let her go first and the men caught her... killed her... The sorceress went back to the village and told the others what happened and about the passage. No one cared... But it's still there today. I've seen it, and the men still know nothing of it.&quot;<br>
<br>
::The fact that the woman knew so much made Sartha raise and brow and she looked down at the woman in curiousity, only to gasp, her eyes going wide. She placed the woman upon the ground and the woman sat up, raising a brow::<br>
<br>
&quot;Something wrong?&quot;<br>
<br>
::Sartha studied the woman for a moment before finding her voice::<br>
<br>
&quot;Red?&quot;<br>
<br>
::the woman's eyes widened::<br>
<br>
&quot;Princess?!&quot;  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/usheyala.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sheyala</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 82<br> <font color=#993300>(1/21/01 2:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=125.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ::Deep in the Forests:::</span><hr size=1> ::Anya finally caught up to the party holding Shey.  Shey was just a leauge ahead, but Anya dared not use mindspeech, for they would both be discovered.  The wolf slowly followed the party until they all reached a dark palace, black as obsidian.  It absorbed all light, or what light there was.  the lands turned dark and desolate, scrub was even hard to find and it was harder and harder for Anya to hunt, though she didn't care, she noticed that Shey hadn't been fed for days..::<br>
