::Shey looked back as she felt a new presence among them...Anya..it had to be.  She smiled but said nothing as they rode on.  All she could do really was look at the dark palace with remorse and horror.  because again it was mostly her fault:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tiger4157>Tiger4157</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 109<br> <font color=#993300>(1/21/01 8:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=125.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ::Deep in the Forests:::</span><hr size=1> ::They had finally made their way to the passage as darkness fell. They hadn't spoken since they had recognized each other. Both had thought the other dead long ago. By now, Red had gained enough strength to walk on her own and so they walked through the forests side-by-side, Veyriean trailing behind them. A day into their walk, Sartha couldn't take it any longer and turned to Red::<br>
